comments: Brown (TOR) places a resting forearm to DeRozan's (CHI) side and immediately removes it at the start of his upward shooting motion.
Vucevic (CHI) places his forearm against Barnes' (TOR) side and marginal contact occurs during Barnes' drive to the basket.
Barnes (TOR) steps out of bounds while still in possession of the ball.
Trent Jr. (TOR) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Barnes (TOR) briefly grasps and then quickly releases Vucevic's (CHI) jersey as Vucevic rolls to the basket.

Brown (TOR) maintains a legal guarding position during Dosunmu's (CHI) drive to the basket.  When Dosunmu attempts the shot, Brown briefly places his forearm against his body but the contact is marginal.

Dosunmu (CHI) reaches for the rebound and makes slight contact with Brown's (TOR) head.  Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Caruso (CHI) initiates contact with Barnes' (TOR) arm that affects his driving shot attempt.
Quickley (TOR) jumps from point A to point B and initiates contact with DeRozan's (CHI) body, which affects his shot attempt at the basket.
Caruso (CHI) is in a legal guarding position and Barnes (TOR) loses control of the ball on his own.
Barnes (TOR) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Schroder (TOR) moves slightly forward and marginal body contact occurs with White (CHI) as they come together during his driving shot attempt.
Trent Jr. (TOR) places his hands on Caruso's (CHI) hip with little extension and the contact is marginal.
Caruso (CHI) maintains verticality and absorbs the contact as incidental foot-to-foot contact occurs during Barnes' (TOR) layup attempt.
Barrett (TOR) brings his arm into White's (CHI) path and immediately slides his hand off as White moves up the floor in transition.
